Descartes has an Irregular Imagination I am unjust in blaming the for:
 using the imagination, and allowing themselves to be entirely guided by the imagination in their reasonings.  There are two kinds of imagination:
 the imagination based on permanent, irresistible, and universal principles  Examples are the habitual transition from causes to effects, and from effects to causes. These are the foundation of all our thoughts and actions.
